Jenna Etheridge, News24Cape Town - A manhunt has been launched for two armed robbers who made off with a "substantial" amount of cash from a bank in Stella, North West police said on Tuesday. One of the suspects was believed to be a former employee of the bank, said police spokesperson Captain Paul Ramaloko.He entered the bank under the pretense that he wanted to inspect a safe door, as he was currently employed by a security company contracted to do the job.His accomplice then joined him. They held staff at gunpoint and took the cash from the safe.The pair fled in a nearby vehicle.Ramaloko said the identity of one of the suspects was known.Police were investigating.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.